==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interrogative
<hw>In`ter*rog"a*tive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>interrogativus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>interrogatif</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Denoting a question; expressed in the form of a question; <as>as,
an <ex>interrogative</ex> sentence; an <ex>interrogative</ex>
pronoun.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interrogative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interrogative
<hw>In`ter*rog"a*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A word
used in asking questions; as, <xex>who</xex>? <xex>which</xex>?
<xex>why</xex>?</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interrogatively</ent>⟦br⟧
